citation: Proclamation under the Public Sector Superannuation (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2009 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Public Sector Superannuation (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2009

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2(2) of the Public Sector Superannuation (Miscellaneous Amendments) Act 2009 fix 1 October 2010 as the day on which the provisions of Parts 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 , 8 , 10 , 12 , 14 , 15 and 16 of that Act commence.

13 September 2010

PETER G. UNDERWOOD

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

MICHAEL AIRD

Treasurer

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 22 September 2010

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Treasury and Finance.
